strings.Value: "You know, I'm a {mf|baron|baroness|king|queen}! It's not polite to kick me out when we're in my dominions!"
"Watch your tongue. I don't remember giving you permission to take that tone with me."
"That was a fine way to wake up – for both of us! Well, so long!"
"You almost fell on me? Hmm, now that's something I wouldn't mind…"
{n}Still half-asleep, you slip on your gear and suddenly hear the angry snap of a tail against the bed post. Looking up, you lock eyes with Kalikke, glowering and embarrassed.{/n}
"{name}! You and Kanerah... I mean... we suddenly switched, and I... could you please get dressed faster?!"
{n}Kalikke turns pale, then nods.{/n} "As you wish. I'm sorry. And now let me freshen up and clean up the house…"

"If I throw water on you, would it be considered high treason?" {n}Kalikke covers her mouth and bursts out laughing.{/n} "We accidentally switched in our sleep! I almost fell on top of you when I came out of the portal! We've never had such a silly switch before…"
"Yeah, right. So you and my sister... ah, doesn't matter! Goodbye!"
"You know what, Kanerah is enough for you! Of course, my sister usually shares everything with me... Oh, what am I saying! That's it, goodbye, {mf|Your Grace|Your Grace|Your Highness|Your Highness}!"
